        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "10. Flaring of gas is prohibited. The State Forester grants an exception to the prohibition on open fires for the flaring of natural gas when the following conditions are met. Unless flaring is needed for safety purposes, flaring pursuant to this exception shall not be done on days that are \"red flag days\" as determined by the National Weather Service or on days when the sustained wind is in excess of 25 miles per hour in the area.",
            "block_bbox": [
                237,
                763,
                1069,
                885
            ],
            "block_id": 11,
            "block_order": 12,
            "group_id": 11,
            "block_polygon_points": [
                [
                    237.0,
                    763.0
                ],
                [
                    1069.0,
                    763.0
                ],
                [
                    1069.0,
                    885.0
                ],
                [
                    237.0,
                    885.0
                ]
            ]
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "11. The day is not a \"red flag day\" as determined by the National Weather Service and the sustained wind is not in excess of 25 miles per hour in the area.",
            "block_bbox": [
                237,
                892,
                1070,
                940
            ],
            "block_id": 12,
            "block_order": 13,
            "group_id": 12,
            "block_polygon_points": [
                [
                    237.0,
                    892.0
                ],
                [
                    1070.0,
                    892.0
                ],
                [
                    1070.0,
                    940.0
                ],
                [
                    237.0,
                    940.0
                ]
            ]
        },
        {
            "block_label": "text",
            "block_content": "12. The local fire department and county dispatch are notified at least 24 hours in advance of anticipated releases that will result in flaring. If flaring is done by an automated system then the schedule of flaring shall be provided to the local fire department and county dispatch. The area is mowed and maintained at a length not to exceed 4 inches and all other flammable products or debris shall be cleared in the area for a distance of one and one half times the height of the stack.",
            "block_bbox": [
                238,
                948,
                1069,
                1094
            ],
            "block_id": 13,
            "block_order": 14,
            "group_id": 13,
            "block_polygon_points": [
                [
                    238.0,
                    948.0
                ],
                [
                    1069.0,
                    948.0
                ],
                [
                    1069.0,
                    1094.0
                ],
